review.description: Great food, great music, what's not to love.  I do wish there was more produce options and not so overpriced but over all we love going to each week
review.author: Amanda P.

review.description: Great market on Wednesdays from 2:30 to ? On Wednesdays.  2018 stalls are very good for baked breads, wine tasting, food trucks, produce and even rare items like delicious homemade kimchi and korean veggies!  Not all the same venders as larger saturday lafayette market so each have their own characteristics.
review.author: Foster F.

review.description: Nice variety of local goods and wares. Slight increase in street traffic on market days but police assist in traffic control and pedestrian crossing. Many of the vendors participate in the other local farmer's markets. A great way to get groceries for the second half of the week. Get up-to-the-minute updates from their Twitter account http://twitter.com/#!/wlfarmersmkt. Sign up at the booth to get your free West Lafayette Farmers Market reusable grocery bag (on  your 3rd visit). Buy local!
review.author: Jeremy S.
